== Notice of Discussion of Rules for RfC on GMO food safety ==

<div class="floatleft" style="margin-bottom:0">[[File:Ambox warning orange.svg|48px|alt=|link=]]</div>A discussion is taking place [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User_talk:The_Wordsmith#GMO_RfC here] about a proposed RfC on GMO food safety language based on the five proposals at GM crops [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk:Genetically_modified_crops#General_agreement_sentence.2C_continued here]. This RfC will affect the current language in paragraph 3 of this article.  <span style="font-family:Courier New;font-size:3">[[User:The Wordsmith|'''The Wordsmith''']]</span><sup>[[User talk:The Wordsmith|Talk to me]]</sup> and [[User:Laser_brain|<font color="purple">'''Laser brain'''</font>]] [[User_talk:Laser_brain|<font color="purple">(talk)</font>]] have graciously volunteered to oversee the RfC.  In addition to discussing the rules, The Wordsmith has created a proposed RfC [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:The_Wordsmith/GMORFC here].  This is <i>not</i> notice that the RfC has begun.  --[[User:David Tornheim|David Tornheim]] ([[User talk:David Tornheim|talk]]) 08:21, 2 May 2016 (UTC)

